@page
@model CookiePolicy
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Cookie Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    This website uses cookies and similar technologies to provide core functionality, to remember your preferences,
    to provide analytics and to enable authentication. This Cookie Policy explains the types of cookies we use, why
    we use them, and how you can control cookie settings.
</p>

<h2>What are cookies?</h2>
<p>
    Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your web browser. They can be "session" cookies (deleted when
    you close your browser) or "persistent" cookies (remain on your device for a fixed period). Cookies may be set by
    this site (first-party cookies) or by third-parties (third-party cookies).
</p>

<h2>Why we use cookies</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Essential cookies: required for security, sign-in and basic site functionality.</li>
    <li>Preference cookies: remember choices you make (language, cookie consent, UI settings).</li>
    <li>Analytics cookies: help us understand how the site is used so we can improve performance and user experience.</li>
    <li>Authentication cookies: used by identity providers to sign you in and keep you signed in securely.</li>
</ul>

